en_808020_0	To coincide with the National Drug Prevention Week, a group of 21 Army personnel, of the 14 (Volunteer) Gemunu Watch, 20 Policemen, 30 state officials and 20 civilians recently listened to a lecture on ‘Use of drugs and illegal transport of them’, organized at the 14 Gemunu Watch (GW) auditorium in the 58 Division Headquarters in Galle.
en_808020_1	The event got underway following instructions given by Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Commander, Security Forces - West (SF-West) to Major General Jayantha Gunaratne, General Officer Commanding, 58 Division.
en_808020_2	Prisons Superintendent at Galle, Mr Jagath Chandana Weerasinghe, together with a few rehabilitated drug addicts who are now free contributed to the lecture sessions during the arrangement.
